# 2026-06-05 — Read-only domain: pitfalls selectable, cohorts locked, mapping bulk-exclude gated

## Refine read-only (PUBLISHED / IN-REVIEW / viewer) UI gates for Pitfalls, Cohorts and Mapping

**Context:** When a domain version is read-only (non-DRAFT lifecycle status —
e.g. PUBLISHED — older inactive version, or a viewer role), the declarative
gates in `permissions.css` (`body:is(.read-only-version, .role-viewer)`) lock
write surfaces. Three gaps surfaced:

1. **Pitfalls** — the pattern checkboxes (`.pitfall-chk`) were caught by the
   generic "disable all form inputs" rule, so a reader on a PUBLISHED version
   could not select patterns to run. Running a pitfalls analysis is a
   read-only operation (the backend `/ontology/pitfalls/analyze` endpoint is in
   `_STATUS_GATE_OPEN_SUFFIXES`, so it is allowed on locked versions), so the
   checkboxes must stay selectable.
2. **Cohorts** — neither the design page (Ontology → Cohorts) write buttons nor
   the Digital-Twin run-page write actions were gated, so a read-only domain
   still allowed creating/editing rules and materialising outputs. The DT page
   is deliberately exempt from the generic form rule, so cohort write controls
   needed explicit gates that also fire there.
3. **Mapping designer** — the bulk `Auto-Exclude` / `Include excluded` buttons
   (added in the mapping-designer bulk-actions work) were missing from the
   read-only gate list, unlike the other designer buttons (reset / auto-map /
   save).

**Changes:**

1. `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css` — added `:not(.pitfall-chk)`
   to the generic read-only form-input disable selector so pitfalls pattern
   checkboxes stay interactive on locked versions.
2. `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css` — added `#mappingAutoExclude`
   and `#mappingIncludeExcluded` to the mapping-designer read-only gate list.
3. `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css` — added a new Cohorts gate
   block neutralising the create/edit/materialise controls
   (`#cohortNewBtn`, `#cohortSaveBtn`, `#cohortAddPathBtn`,
   `#cohortAddConstraintBtn`, `#cohortOutputsBtn`, `#cohortMaterializeBtn`) plus
   the dynamically-rendered link/hop/where/compat add+remove buttons
   (`.cohort-link-del`, `.cohort-hop-add`, `.cohort-hop-del`,
   `.cohort-hop-where-add`, `.cohort-hop-where-del`, `.cohort-hop-where-sample`,
   `.cohort-row-del`, `.cohort-sample`). The saved-rules picker and the
   read-only Preview / Trace / Explain actions stay interactive.
4. `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_cohorts.html` — added
   `id="cohortNewBtn"`, `id="cohortAddPathBtn"`, `id="cohortAddConstraintBtn"`
   so the design-page write buttons can be targeted by the gate.
5. `src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_cohorts.html` — added
   `id="cohortOutputsBtn"` so the run-page Configure-outputs button can be
   gated (Materialise already had `id="cohortMaterializeBtn"`).

**Scope note:** "Cohorts read-only" is implemented as: cannot create or edit a
rule (design page) and cannot persist outputs or materialise (run page).
Read-only inspection — loading a saved rule, Preview, Path trace, Explain —
remains available. Server-side, mutating cohort endpoints are not yet
status-gated; this change is the UI half. Real enforcement for cohort writes on
locked versions is a follow-up if required.

**Files modified:**
- `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css`
- `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_cohorts.html`
- `src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_cohorts.html`

**Tests:**

```
uv run pytest -q --ignore=tests/e2e --ignore=tests/property --ignore=tests/live_integration --no-cov
# 2467 passed, 22 warnings in 20.72s
```

E2E (`tests/e2e/security/test_permissions_flows.py`) and property/live suites
were not run here — they require a Playwright browser + a reachable Databricks
workspace. These changes are CSS + Jinja-template only (no Python behaviour
change), and the full in-process unit + integration suite is green.
